<div id="review_1453693017" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1453693017" />
    <a title="Jeanne Johnston" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/27559164-jeanne-johnston"><img alt="Jeanne Johnston" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1389888765p2/27559164.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1453693017?book_show_action=true">Nov 27, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jeanne Johnston" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jeanne Johnston" href="/user/show/27559164-jeanne-johnston">Jeanne Johnston</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1453693017" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1578283666545030507">Odd to read in order of the story when the books are written so out of order. This clearly came late, but it&apos;s as though nothing from the prior book (Hastur Lord) ever happened. Countless references to the Sharra Rebellion, not a peep about Rinaldo and that whole mess. Regis even has two sons now, but not a word was said about Stelli, presumably still off cavorting with the Chieri. It&apos;s odd and disjointed... but I was so glad to be back into familiar territory that I didn&apos;t care. <br/><br/>So glad Lew is </span>
  <span id="freeText1578283666545030507" style="display:none">Odd to read in order of the story when the books are written so out of order. This clearly came late, but it's as though nothing from the prior book (Hastur Lord) ever happened. Countless references to the Sharra Rebellion, not a peep about Rinaldo and that whole mess. Regis even has two sons now, but not a word was said about Stelli, presumably still off cavorting with the Chieri. It's odd and disjointed... but I was so glad to be back into familiar territory that I didn't care. <br /><br />So glad Lew is himself again, worried about Dio, and who doesn't love a love story? Javanne is more of a bitch than ever and Gabriel, I didn't remember being so petty. Mikhail's older brothers were surprising jerks, younger sister Ariel a basket case (again, no mention of the previous book and her being kidnapped). The rest is as complex as trying to figure out who on Darkover is related to whom. Easier to say just everyone. <br /><br />Obviously, this story has to continue, so off I go to crack open the next book. </span>
  <a data-text-id="1578283666545030507" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


