        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer649953949" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12190507153469205649">Ah, now I see why I found the third book in this trilogy - Traitor&apos;s Sun - somewhat unsatisfactory. It doesn&apos;t really get on with the &quot;exciting changes in Darkover society&quot; which are foretold in the first book! There are some advantages in reading a trilogy in reverse order, you tend to spot details which are meaningful but which you might not notice if reading the books in sequence!<br/><br/>This is the best of the three I think. I loved having so much detail about home life on Darkover, and Margaret Alt</span>
  <span id="freeText12190507153469205649" style="display:none">Ah, now I see why I found the third book in this trilogy - Traitor's Sun - somewhat unsatisfactory. It doesn't really get on with the "exciting changes in Darkover society" which are foretold in the first book! There are some advantages in reading a trilogy in reverse order, you tend to spot details which are meaningful but which you might not notice if reading the books in sequence!<br /><br />This is the best of the three I think. I loved having so much detail about home life on Darkover, and Margaret Alton is a refreshing foil to the other women.</span>
  <a data-text-id="12190507153469205649" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

